HEADWORD: Permistion
<hw>Per*mis"tion</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*m⟦icr⟧s"ch⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>permistio</ets>, <ets>permixtio</ets>, fr.
<ets>permiscere</ets>, <ets>permistum</ets>, and <ets>permixtum</ets>.
See <er>Permiscible</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of mixing; the state of
being mingled; mixture.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>permixtion</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

